$ VMCreate.exe

`VMCreate.exe` can be used to quickly create → Windows/optional-features/Hyper-V virtual machines from the following «curated» virtual machine images (as of March 2024):
  • Windows 10 MSIX packaging environment
  • → https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/downloads/virtual-machines[Windows 11 dev environment]
  • → Linux/distributions/Ubuntu 18.04/20.04 and 22.04 (all LTS)

The *Windows 11 dev environment* is an evaluation copy of Windows 11 Entrprise with:
  • → Windows/development/Visual-Studio[Visual Studio] 2022 Community → Windows/development/Visual-Studio/editions[Edition] with UWP, .NET Desktop, Azure, and Windows App SDK for C# workloads enabled
  • → Windows/Subsystem-for-Linux 2 enabled with Ubuntu installed
  • → Windows/Terminal installed
  • → Windows/development/developer-mode[Developer mode] enabled

Other evaluation versions of Windows that can be installed with `VMCreate.exe` include:
  • → https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/evalcenter/evaluate-windows-10-enterprise[Windows 10 Enterprise]
  • → https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/evalcenter/evaluate-windows-11-enterprise[Windows 11 Enterprise]

sa:

 `→ Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Hyper-V`
